			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: VP Quest questions.<a name="69295"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 9 04 7:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At level 67 I found the Protectors of Zek not too difficult once I'd worked out a strategy. I have around 4K HP/ 4K mana, and max defensive AA's, but realistically these didn't knock me below 80% health using the following method, and having enough mana to fade two or three times should be fine. The power source dropped for me on my fourth kill.
<br />

<br />
A quick bulletpoint list of my actions.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Get full mana and a Virtue.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Enter KD and run to a corner in the arena (I used the right side, but that was just personal preference) then fade off agro
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Wait until the roamers path to the opposite side of the arena and go to the PoZ door (Using SSoQ works fine to avoid picking up agro as roamers come close whilst you are waiting)
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Approach door, open, and back off a little (you will get aggro if you stand too close) 
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Pacify any two of the three Protectors with SSoQ, and pull the third (I use Harmony of Sound to pull, but that's just personal preference).
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Path straight out from the door before heading back to your corner (to avoid agroing the static guards)
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Charm (Call of the Banshee) the Protector. At this point you want to pull two guards onto him. One of the static spawns by the ramp leading out of the arena was a cleric, so I tended to avoid those.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Switch in a stringed instrument and sing your preferred HP regen song (I used my Fungus tunic aswell).
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Keep the Protector targetted and when charm breaks run in circles and recharm. You will have no direct aggro from the other guard(s) so as soon as you recharm and get hit by one of them you can move back as the Protector agro's both.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Sing your HP regen song. You should be able to get back to full health (or near) before charm breaks again.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Repeat this until the Protector gets to under 15% HP (you will need to occassionaly pull more guards onto him, he will kill two or three guards during this process). At 10% to 15% don't pull a second guard onto him, leave him fighting one at a time (unless the single guard looks likely to die - the protectors have insane regen so don't leave them unengaged even for a moment).
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Once the Protector's HP drops below 15% or so he will be ready to flee. The next time that charm breaks after his HP drops below this point you should charm the other guard, and not the protector.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Set your pet on the fleeing protector and switch to percussion and start DoT'ing him. You may pick up an add or two as the Protector paths across the arena, but since they are undamaged you will not be summoned (until your charm breaks, so just recharm the old pet or summon kite the protector from this point on).
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Fade off agro once the protector dies.
<br />

<br />
Not neccessarily as easy as pure DoT kiting, but it worked for me.
<br />

<br />
Good luck.
<br />

<br />
Xeona</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
