				<td colspan="2"><span>Don,
<br />

<br />
Every time charm breaks you will be summoned, and that's why you need to keep him targetted for a quick recharm, and regen as much HP as possible between charm breaks. 
<br />

<br />
Once the protectors HP falls below the magic level (15%?), and there is no second mob around (i.e. you've charmed the guard, instead of the protector) then he will flee, so summoning is not a problem - that's why it is important to have just the protector and one other mob involved when you want to finish him off.
<br />

<br />
Sorry is that what you were asking or have I missed your point?
<br />

